# Phase
phases = {
    'Phase1 ()': ('phase1_return_pct', 'phase1_win'),
    'Phase2 ()': ('phase2_return_pct', 'phase2_win'),
    'Phase3-1% (-1%)': ('phase3_1pct_return_pct', 'phase3_1pct_win'),
    'Phase3-2% (-2%)': ('phase3_2pct_return_pct', 'phase3_2pct_win'),
    'Phase3-3% (-3%)': ('phase3_3pct_return_pct', 'phase3_3pct_win'),
}

summary_data = []
for phase_name, (return_col, win_col) in phases.items():
    win_rate = df[win_col].sum() / len(df) * 100
    avg_return = df[return_col].mean()
    median_return = df[return_col].median()
    
    summary_data.append({
        'Phase': phase_name,
        '(%)': f"{win_rate:.1f}",
        '(%)': f"{avg_return:.2f}",
        '(%)': f"{median_return:.2f}",
        '': df[win_col].sum(),
        '': len(df) - df[win_col].sum()
    })

summary_df = pd.DataFrame(summary_data)
print(summary_df.to_string(index=False))

print("\n" + "=" * 80)
print("")
print("=" * 80)
print(df['category'].value_counts())

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(18, 10))
axes = axes.flatten()

return_cols = [
    ('phase1_return_pct', 'Phase1 ()'),
    ('phase2_return_pct', 'Phase2 ()'),
    ('phase3_1pct_return_pct', 'Phase3-1% (-1%)'),
    ('phase3_2pct_return_pct', 'Phase3-2% (-2%)'),
    ('phase3_3pct_return_pct', 'Phase3-3% (-3%)')
]

for idx, (col, title) in enumerate(return_cols):
    ax = axes[idx]
    
    # 
    ax.hist(df[col].dropna(), bins=20, color='steelblue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    
    # 
    mean_val = df[col].mean()
    ax.axvline(mean_val, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f': {mean_val:.2f}%')
    ax.axvline(0, color='gray', linestyle='-', linewidth=1)
    
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_xlabel(' (%)', fontsize=10)
    ax.set_ylabel('', fontsize=10)
    ax.legend()
    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# 
axes[-1].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 
win_rates = []
phase_names = []

for phase_name, (_, win_col) in phases.items():
    win_rate = df[win_col].sum() / len(df) * 100
    win_rates.append(win_rate)
    phase_names.append(phase_name.replace(' ', '\n'))

# 
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

colors = ['green' if wr >= 50 else 'red' for wr in win_rates]
bars = ax.bar(phase_names, win_rates, color=colors, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')

# 50%
ax.axhline(50, color='black', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5, label='50%')

# 
for bar, wr in zip(bars, win_rates):
    height = bar.get_height()
    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height + 1,
            f'{wr:.1f}%', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')

ax.set_title('Phase', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
ax.set_ylabel(' (%)', fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylim(0, 100)
ax.legend()
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
